content:
Navigate from a FlexCard with the Navigate Action

To navigate to an external web address, or within Lightning Experience, Lightning communities, or the Salesforce mobile app from a Navigate Action element on a FlexCard.

Drag an Action element into a state in the FlexCard Designer.
Select Navigate from the Action Type dropdown and choose a page reference type from the Target dropdown.
Configure settings and options unique to your selected Target.
If the Target is App, enter the App Target in the format: standard__[appName] or [namespace]__[appName].
If the Target is Component, enter the Component Name as [namespace]__[componentName].
Specify where to open the target page from the Open Target In dropdown.
Configure other options common among all action properties.
Style your action element with the Style panel and see FlexCards Action Style Properties.
title: Navigating with FlexCards
